@node "EXTDESIGN" "Usage of external design files"

                 @{u}@{b}Support for External Design Files (V1.3)@{uu}@{ub}

Since V1.3 it is possible to use external design files to customize the output
of mULTI-tOP. 

To let this feature work you have to define a valid path to your design files
in mULTI-tOP.cfg. mULTI-tOP checks for the following files inside this path:

    UL_BYTES.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Bytes Uploader Bull
    DL_BYTES.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Bytes Downloader Bull
    UL_FILES.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Files Uploader Bull
    DL_FILES.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Files Downloader Bull
      UL_CPS.DSG  ---> Template for the Top CPS Uploading Bull
      DL_CPS.DSG  ---> Template for the Top CPS Downloading Bull
     CALLERS.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Callers Bull
    MESSAGES.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Message Writer Bull
 NUKED_BYTES.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Nuked Bytes Bull
 NUKED_FILES.DSG  ---> Template for the Top Nuked Files Bull
       CHATS.DSG  ---> Template for the Top SysOp-Chatters Bull
       HACKS.DSG  ---> Template for the Top overall hacks Bull

Whenever one of these files could not be opened/found, mULTI-tOP uses the
internal layout engine, so it's not neccessary to use these templates.

A design file is just an ASCII/ANSI/WHATEVER file which represents the output
you wish to have for the according statistics. I would recommend to first 
design your statistics with dummy values and after you've finished the design
replace your dummy values with the special command strings described below.

Every design file has special command strings which will be replaced by
the according datas from your user.datas. 

Every command follows the same syntax:

                                 %WW-CM-PL

 %: Is the Introducer for a special command. Please note that you *MUST*
    end every command with a trailing space ( ), or the command won't be
    recognized!!!

WW: Width in chars for the field. Must be always 2 digits. If the string to
    be inserted is longer than this value, it will be cutted. If the string
    is shorter than this value, it will be filled with spaces.

CM: Command Parameter. This indicates the value which will be inserted, i.e.
    UN stands for UserName. A complete list is below. 

PL: Place-Indicator. Enter here the place of the user, i.e. 01 stands for the
    top guy, the NUMBER ONE ;)

An example: 
                                 %20-UN-01

Will be replaced with a 20 chars long string containing the UserName of Rank 1
for the given statistics.

The command parameter has a double function. If you write the command parameter
all in upper-case (i.e. UN), the string to be inserted will be LEFT-ALIGNED.
If you however write the command string in lower-case (i.e. un), the string to
be inserted will be RIGHT-ALIGNED! 

This works with all suppported commands. 

Here is a list of all currently supported commands:

UN - Username
UL - Userlocation/-group
UB - User uploaded bytes
DB - User downloaded Bytes
UF - User uploaded files
DF - User download files
UC - Upload CPS
DC - Download CPS
CL - Callers
MW - Messages written
NB - Nuked Bytes
NF - Nuked Files
CH - Chats
HA - Hacks

All of the following commands ignore the place value, as they are global 
values taken from your BBS:

BU - Total bytes uploaded to your system
BD - Total bytes downloaded from your system
FU - Total files uploaded to your system
FD - Total files Downloaded from your system
SC - Total Calls 
TU - Total Users in BBS
TM - Total Messages written
$$ - Program Name and Version
LD - Last Update - Date (DD-MMM-YY) (V1.31)
LT - Last Update - Time (HH:MM:SS) (V1.31)
Y2 - Last Update - Date (MM-DD-YYYY) (V1.32)
SM - System/BBS Name (V1.32)

Here are an example for a top 3 CPS Upload list:

---

1. %20-UN-01 %06-uc-01 CPS
2. %20-UN-02 %06-uc-02 CPS
3. %20-UN-03 %06-uc-03 CPS

---

Save this in your external design directory under the filename UL_CPS.DSG 
and start Multi-Top. The result should look like this:

1. XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX XXXXXX CPS
2. XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX     XXXX CPS
3. XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX       XXXX CPS

More examples are in the ExampleDesigns drawer, but I think it is very
easy to configure and use, isn't it ?

Feel free to send me your custom designs, it would be nice to release later
versions with a bunch of designs ;) 

Just click @{"HERE" LINK "CONTACT"} to get my contact address!
@endnode

